TITLE: American soccer journalist Grant Wahl 'laughing at a joke' on Twitter minutes before collapse, witness says
SUMMARY: Veteran soccer journalist Grant Wahl was laughing and joking with colleagues not long before suddenly passing away during a quarterfinal match at the World Cup in Qatar.

TITLE: Prince Harry's Netflix doc includes Princess Diana's interview despite Prince William's pleas to never air it
SUMMARY: Netflix dropped the first three episodes of their docuseries on the Duke and Duchess of Sussex titled "Harry & Meghan." It features clips from Princess Diana's "Panorama" interview.

TITLE: Execution of Iranian protestor may kick off even more violent regime crackdown
SUMMARY: Iran announced the execution of a protester and could well signal the start of an even more violent phase of its crackdown.

TITLE: Library patrons rip nixing of Christmas tree: 'We want equal representation in this town'
SUMMARY: Two library patrons in Dedham, Massachusetts, sounded off to "Jesse Watters Primetime" after a branch decided to not put up a Christmas tree this year.

TITLE: Chicago dog goes viral on TikTok after owner has pup's fur dyed green to resemble Grinch
SUMMARY: A dog owner in Chicago has faced backlash after posting a TikTok video of her dog with newly dyed red-and-green fur — resembling the Grinch ahead of Christmas 2022.

TITLE: Hillary Clinton still owes Tammy Wynette an apology
SUMMARY: Tammy Wynette is back in the cultural spotlight thanks to a new Showtime series about her tumultuous marriage with George Jones.

TITLE: ‘Active and cuddly’ Staffie in Los Angeles ready to find new family: He’s ‘best of both worlds’
SUMMARY: Looking to bring a pet home for the holidays? Three-year-old American Staffordshire mix Oreo is up for adoption at Best Friends Animal Society in Los Angeles.

TITLE: Are progressives demonizing incoming Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu's right-wing coalition?
SUMMARY: A campaign is said to be underway by left-wing and liberal groups in the U.S. to destabilize Benjamin Netanyahu's chances of forming a right-wing government.

TITLE: 'Twitter Files' most overlooked finding? That Dorsey, Zuckerberg and half of America shrug at censorship
SUMMARY: Elon Musk has been releasing parts of the so-called 'Twitter Files' for more than a week. But much of the country, including liberal media and major tech CEOs are all but ignoring them.

TITLE: American soccer journalist Grant Wahl dies while covering FIFA World Cup in Qatar
SUMMARY: Grant Wahl, famed American soccer journalist, died while covering the FIFA World Cup in Qatar at age 48, his brother believes he was killed and is pleading for help.
